## Mailbox settings
IMAPAccount gmail
Host imap.gmail.com
User simon.podhajsky@gmail.com
PassCmd "security find-generic-password -s mbsync-gmail-password -w"
AuthMechs LOGIN
UseIMAPS yes
CertificateFile /Users/Simon/gmail/gmail.pem
PipelineDepth 3

IMAPStore gmail-remote
Account gmail

MaildirStore gmail-local
Path ~/gmail/
Inbox ~/gmail/Inbox
Trash ~/gmail/PrimaryArchive

## Global options
Sync Pull
Create Slave
CopyArrivalDate yes
SyncState *
FSync no

## Channels
# Necessary channels
Channel gmail-Inbox
Master :gmail-remote:
Slave :gmail-local:
Patterns "NonPrimary" "Primary" "PrimaryArchive" "Yale"
Sync All
Expunge Both

# Drafts -- those should be sync'd, but contain canned responses, so be careful
Channel gmail-Drafts
Master :gmail-remote:[Gmail]/Drafts
Slave :gmail-local:Drafts
Sync All
Expunge Slave

# Gmail automatically stores messages sent with its SMTP -> never push
Channel gmail-Sent
Master ":gmail-remote:[Gmail]/Sent Mail"
Slave :gmail-local:Sent
Sync Pull

# First experiment with dual sync
Channel gmail-Plusmail
Master :gmail-remote:Plusmail
Slave :gmail-local:Plusmail
MaxMessages 1000
Sync All

Group gmail
Channel gmail-Inbox
Channel gmail-Drafts
Channel gmail-Sent
Channel gmail-Plusmail
